          <div class="date" style="text-align:right;float:right;">6.11.2004</div><br /><br />
     
     
     <font class="TallRed">Thank Gawd for student discounts!<a name="108693187684183080">&nbsp;</a></font>
		<div class="blackjustified" style="background-color:#eeeeee;padding:5px 5px 5px 5px;border-top:3px solid #cccccc;border-bottom:1px solid #333333;border-left:1px solid #cccccc;border-right:1px solid #cccccc;">
          <a href="http://wired.com/news/mac/0,2125,63774,00.html?tw=wn_tophead_12">Wired News: Apple Touts Super-Cooled G5s</a>. Yes kids, I've been waiting for this moment for a couple years now.  This is where I say SCREW THE PC I'M MIGRATING.  Because of my recent change in major I will be getting some assistance from my family to get myself a new computer. Currently, the fastest machine I have is a 1.4ghz Athlon with 128mb video card and 768mb of ram.  <br /><br />This new G5 will spank my old machine and then tell it that it has no father.<br /><br />First of all, the speed of the Front Side Bus (The bus via which a processor<br />communicates with its RAM and chipset;) on the mac will be as fast as the cpu in my main machine: 1.4ghz. the chip<u>s</u> in the mac will be 2.5 ghz each with 1 gig of ram to back it up. The video card is to drool over: a 9800XT pro with 256mb of SDRAM built in (twice of my other computer). The best part: Apple is <a href="http://www.macrumors.com">rumored</a> to be upgrading their displays.<br /><br /><center><b>[IMAGE KILLED]</b><br />imagine this beauty sitting on your desk, 20 inches of pure sex.</center><br /><br />And all this time you thought E3R was made with a mac. No sir. It's only going to get better from here. They ship in July and near the end of this month Apple will be declaring whats new for this year. While some <a href="http://www.blogger.com/profile/3571774">people</a> are a little pissed off about not getting the dual 3.0 updates promised by Steve Jobs last year for this year, they might just forgive him when they take one of these new displays for a spin. The sizes for these suckers start at 20" and end at 30". While I think 30" would be overkill, 20" would do me fine. I know there are a lot of Mac-haters out there and I'm waiting for them to show their <a href="http://www.blogger.com/profile/3572669">faces</a>. <br /><br />My <b>BOLD</b> prediction: While I don't think that Apple will be on top, I certainly don't think Microsoft will be the world's number one desktop operating system by 2008.<br /><br />
          <div class="byline">
<b>jd.b!</b>&nbsp;@ 1:31 AM [<a href="http://www.devlogik.com/www/E3R_2/blog/2004/06/thank-gawd-for-student-discounts.php" title="permanent link">#</a>|<a href="mailto:devlogik@gmail.com?subject=RE: E3R POST #108693187684183080&body=Hey jd.b!!">e</a>]</div>
