				While I appreciate your concern, I'm most DEFINATELY sure I'm ready for a change. I run Windows, I run Server machines, it's time to go back to my roots man. Furthermore, my major suggests using a mac. <br /><br />FSB = not important? beh, I beg to differ. I understand that Macs use sort of a Virtual FSB but with the speed at which the real FSB runs, I'll be running with a high ceiling. SO I'll never peak 100% cpu usage -- is this a problem? HELL NO.<br /><br />About the dead pixel problem: yes, unfortunately for PC users that IS a problem but I will have AppleCare backin me up. I don't plan on going too large, a 20in will suffice. Since I'm putting up so much money for a computer I might as well get one that will still be kickin by the time my little sister gets into college. I have 5 machines, most of them running linux, I love linux, don't get me wrong, but its time for something new.<br /><br />Besides, I'll be running UNIX anyway. The only difference is that my hardware will be worth twice as much as everyone elses after their hardware goes obsolete. Think of it this way, it's like I'm running a server box with the K Desktop Environment except Aqua is so much better. <br /><br />Its like that quarky little song: "I can do anything you can do but better!" *whistles* yeah, because I will and I'll look better doing too. When it comes down to it, there are no machines that act and feel as a mac. You can theme and mod a PC all ya want, but in the end you're only digging yourself a hole with CPU usage. Whats the friggen point? So, in conclusion here are my reasons for wanting a kick ass machine:<br /><br />1. I've wanted one for over 2 years<br />2. My major is *almost* forcing me to get one (I could be a pain in the ass and reject their wishes but why the hell would I do that?)<br />3. I've become pretty savvy at every other major OS<br />4. My main machine (1.4ghz Athlon 128mb ATI 9600 160GB w/ 768mb DDR) is slowly becoming obsolete and the Windows install is slowly landing on it's knees from all of the worms and virii I've been dodging.<br />5. Windows is boring and when you have 2 servers Linux gets boring too.<br />6. I'm not a computer scientist. I'm a designer. A designer who has been designing for SEVEN years on a PC. I f***ing DESERVE a Mac by now. <br />7. Just Because. Ha.<br />
				<div class="byline"><a href="http://www.devlogik.com/www/E3R_2/blog/2004/06/thank-gawd-for-student-discounts.php#108701825843081753" title="permanent link">#</a> posted by <a href="http://www.blogger.com/profile/2015057">jd.b!</a> @ 1:30 AM</div>
